{"TopicId":153688,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Goofy Physics","CreatedByName":"Mike Mars","CreatedById":157620,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-18T20:12:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mike Mars","CreatedById":157620,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-18T20:12:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022table-layout:fixed;width:1092px;line-height:1.6;color:rgb(39,42,52);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px;margin-top:0px;font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-top:0px;\u0022\u003E\nI just recently upgraded to KSP v1.2.2. \u00A0I intentionally waited until all my mods had upgraded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-top:0px;\u0022\u003E\nI am now encountering a strange problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-top:0px;\u0022\u003E\nIf I land a craft on another world, everything works just fine. \u00A0But when I change focus and then come back, the craft pops up off the surface, then slowly descends and explodes on contact with the surface.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-top:0px;\u0022\u003E\nOn Kerbin, the craft will pop up about a meter or two. \u00A0On Duna, about 100 meters. \u00A0On the Mun, about 2,500 meters.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-top:0px;\u0022\u003E\nHas anybody else run into this issue?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould appreciate any help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-bottom:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:1px dotted;\u0022 title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-18T20:14:31Z\u0022 title=\u002212/18/2016 08:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 18, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Mike Mars\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Espelling, duh!\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-18T20:29:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat mods are you using? I don\u0027t think that I can answer your question, but someone else might be able to if they know the mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-18T20:39:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee what happens when you increase/decrease terrain detail settings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mike Mars","CreatedById":157620,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-18T21:05:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTex_NL,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI changed terrain detail setting from \u0022High\u0022 to \u0022Default\u0022 based on your suggestion, but apparently it had no impact. \u00A0Base still lifted off the surface and slowly descended.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for the suggestion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mike Mars","CreatedById":157620,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T00:40:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have isolated the problem to a specific mod, Pathfinder, and even specific parts in that mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave posted data on that mod\u0027s forum.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gianni1122","CreatedById":170752,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-20T14:44:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157620-mike-mars/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022157620\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157620-mike-mars/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mike Mars\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee if the \u0022ease in\u00A0gravity\u0022 option is on in the settings. I think it\u00A0is used so that when you send\u00A0a craft to the pad, it doesn\u0027t explode when it \u0022settles\u0022. It might help with the 1-2 meter pop ups (maybe\u00A0not the higher jumps though\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/147668-ease-in-gravity/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-20T14:46:07Z\u0022 title=\u002212/20/2016 02:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Gianni1122\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mike Mars","CreatedById":157620,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-20T16:42:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222894421\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482245091\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170752\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gianni1122\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Gianni1122 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157620-mike-mars/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022157620\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157620-mike-mars/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mike Mars\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee if the \u0022ease in\u00A0gravity\u0022 option is on in the settings. I think it\u00A0is used so that when you send\u00A0a craft to the pad, it doesn\u0027t explode when it \u0022settles\u0022. It might help with the 1-2 meter pop ups (maybe\u00A0not the higher jumps though\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/147668-ease-in-gravity/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGianni,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for the response.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe issue is actually part specific. \u00A0There are two base hubs in the Pathfinder mod that have this issue. \u00A0The others work fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have posted this observation on the Pathfinder mod forum. \u00A0Thus far, there has been no response from the developer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have redesigned my Duna base and the new version is in transit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks again for your response.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}